OL,6,FThe method of execution has been
OL,7,Fdescribed by the Alabama attorney
OL,8,Fgeneral's office as the "most painless
OL,9,Fand humane method of execution known
OL,10,Fto man", but the United Nations (UN)
OL,11,Fhas disputed this, saying nitrogen
OL,12,Fhypoxia could "amount to torture" and
OL,13,Fbreak international human rights laws.
OL,15,FThe American Veterinary Medical
OL,16,FAssociation in 2020 euthanasia
OL,17,Fguidelines wrote nitrogen hypoxia is
OL,18,Fnot an acceptable euthanasia method
OL,19,Ffor most mammals because the anoxic
OL,20,Fenvironment is "distressing".
